==Old English==
===Etymology===
''Tiwes'' (''gen'' of [[Tiw|Tīw]]) + [[dæg|dæġ]].  Cognate with Old Frisian ''Tiesdei'', Old High German ''zīostag'' (dialectal German ''Zistig''), Old Norse ''týrsdagr'' (Swedish ''[[tisdag]]'').  Used in translation of the Latin ''[[dies Martis]]''
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'tiwezdæj/

===Noun===
'''Tiwesdæġ'''
